   3 Biological information about nesting aspects inside and outside the
   nest was considered, paying particular attention to year-long activity,
   foraging flights throughout the day for nectar and pollen collection,
   nectar dehydration, oviposition, and pollen preference.
   4 In the study area, X. augusti shows an univoltine life cycle, with a
   peak of nesting between October and December, which coincides with the
   greatest blooming period of the surrounding flora.
   5 From 36 analyzed larval provision samples, 18 pollen types were
