Abstract = {{We surveyed bees inhabiting inland dune and ridge woodlands at 30 sites
   in Worcester County, MD, in 2008 and 2009. We collected and identified
   4878 bees representing 5 families, 31 genera, and 121 species. Here, we
   report data on annual and seasonal variation. Expanding survey efforts
   to include multiple years and seasons served to increase the overall
   number of species encountered, primarily through documenting the
   presence of rare or infrequently collected species. Eighty-eight species
   (73\%) were represented by fewer than 10 individuals; of these 30 were
   represented by a single individual (25\% of the total). The 5 most
   dominant species represented nearly half (48\%) of the total number of
   specimens. We report a list of bee species collected from inland dune
   and ridge woodlands and discuss the presence of apparently
