   Headspace-solid phase microextraction-gas chromatography-mass
   spectrometry (HS-SPME-GC-MS) was used to identify the volatile organic
   compounds (VOCs) of the different flower development stages of L.
   yunnanensis for the evaluation of floral volatile polymorphism. The
   results showed that a total of 40 compounds were identified at four
   different stages. The main aroma-active compounds were 3-carene,
